        },
        "rich_text_Jc4E4r": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Which Hand Engagement Ring Female Traditions Around the World",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Which Hand Engagement Ring Female Traditions Around the World</h2><h3>Countries That Use the Left Hand</h3><p>Regions such as the United States, Canada, the United Kingdom, France, Italy, and Australia traditionally wear engagement rings on the left hand.</p><h3>Countries That Use the Right Hand</h3><p>In Germany, Russia, India, Norway, and parts of Eastern Europe, engagement rings are typically worn on the right hand. If you're researching which hand to wear engagement ring, it’s helpful to look into your cultural background and personal preference.</p>",
            "custom_id": "which-hand",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qtiUNY": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Engagement Ring Placement After the Wedding Ceremony",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Engagement Ring Placement After the Wedding Ceremony</h2>",
            "custom_id": "engagement",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_Vpe8ag": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Engagement_Ring_Placement_After_the_Wedding_Ceremony_376161f6-1df8-4d0f-a5f2-5e6cc74d62da.jpg",
            "text": "<h3>Engagement Ring Before the Ceremony</h3><p>Usually, brides move their engagement ring to the right hand before the ceremony so the wedding band can be placed on the left-hand ring finger first.</p><h3>After the Ceremony</h3><p>Most people place the engagement ring back on top of the wedding band, though this can vary based on style or personal taste.</p>",
